    },
    "image_with_text_MyUkEX": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_FBXHht": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Currently, Jamila is developing her first scripted feature film, which recently received funding and is now in the early stages of production.. </p><p>Her sophomore feature documentary, <a href=\"https://vancouversun.com/entertainment/roots-and-recipes-jamila-pomeroys-new-doc-muzizi-brings-african-flavours-to-the-forefront\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><em>Muzizi</em></span></a>, is now available to watch on <a href=\"https://gem.cbc.ca/\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">CBC Gem</span></a>. As a Writer, Director, Executive Producer and Host, Jamila takes viewers on a vibrant culinary journey through the African diaspora in Vancouver.</p><p>We spent the morning with Jamila at two of her favourite local spots—<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/riseupmarketplace\" title=\"https://www.instagram.com/riseupmarketplace\">Rise Up Marketplace</a> and <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/mah.milkbar/\" title=\"https://www.instagram.com/mah.milkbar/\">Mah Milk Bar</a>—to learn more about her journey as a filmmaker, and her mission to uplift and empower marginalized voices through the power of storytelling. </p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_FBXHht"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/IMG_5769-Enhanced-NR.jpg",
